race.comment: SUBTLE POWER (10) looks to set up nicely on the map here, likely tagging the speed from the low gate without much pressure up front. Her past two starts have been good, beaten a long neck at Pakenham over 1600m last time out when back in trip. Gets every chance here over an ideal distance. QUITE THE LASS (11) ran quite well fresh here over 1507m when working home into a narrow sixth. She hasn't won in a while but will be fitter and this trip suits better. CAT NOIR (8) was just fair fresh at Ararat but goes well here and her best form would be very competitive. PENNINE WAY (2) struggled on tough ground fresh and should do much better this time.
